=== RAW MODEL ANSWER ===
Answer: Step 1: 2-aminophenol + epichlorohydrin, base, gives the glycidyl ether intermediate ArOCH2CH(O)CH2 (o-aminophenyl glycidyl ether). | Step 2: Intramolecular epoxide opening/cyclization (heat or base) furnishes 2-(hydroxymethyl)-3,4-dihydro-2H-1,4-benzoxazine, i.e. HOCH2C1CNc2ccccc2O1. | Step 3: Protect the ring NH (Boc2O) to give N-Boc-HOCH2C1COc2ccccc2N1-type benzoxazine alcohol. | Step 4: Deprotonate the alcohol and O-allylate with allyl bromide (or allyl chloride/NaH) to form the allyl ether Boc-protected intermediate C=CCOCH2C1CN(Boc)c2ccccc2O1. | Step 5: Remove Boc under acid to give the target C=CCOCC1CNc2ccccc2O1.

=== NORMALIZED STUDENT ANSWER ===
